## Summary

| Severity | Count | Pattern |
|---|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | Assert-free (fire-and-forget) |
| 🟠 High | 4 | Assert-not-null only (no value checks) |
| 🟡 Medium | 6+ | Missing negative/edge-case tests |

**Root cause**: Every test follows the same template — call the method, optionally `Assert.IsNotNull`, done. This inflates line coverage to ~95% while verifying almost **zero** behavioral contracts. The fix is straightforward: each test needs assertions on **return values and side-effects**, plus dedicated tests for error paths.
